## Luxury Domestic Staffing and Private Household Management\
\
A unique and highly specific demographic that benefits from mobile NDAs\
is the high-net-worth (HNW) family and their domestic staff. In this\
sector, discretion is a \\"foundational requirement\\". Approximately 95%\
of staff in ultra-high-net-worth households are required to sign NDAs to\
protect personal, financial, and security information.\
\
### The \\"Nuclear\\" vs. \\"Reasonable\\" NDA Conflict\
\
A primary pain point in household management is the \\"nuclear\\" NDA---a\
17-page document drafted by corporate lawyers that treats a nanny or a\
housekeeper as a national security risk. This approach often alienates\
top-tier talent, who may withdraw their applications because the\
document prevents them from even mentioning their general job\
responsibilities to future employers.\
\
A mobile-first solution targeted at household managers allows for the\
deployment of \\"reasonable\\" NDAs. These documents focus specifically on\
what matters---financial details, family schedules, and security\
codes---while explicitly allowing the staff member to describe their job\
duties (e.g., managing a 15,000 sq. ft. estate) for career advancement.\
\
### The On-Site Contractor Challenge\
\
Household managers and personal assistants are responsible for\
on-boarding a constant stream of vendors: pool cleaners, caterers,\
interior designers, and security consultants. Mandating that these\
vendors sign an NDA on a tablet or smartphone as they enter the property\
ensures that \\"local chatter\\" and accidental disclosure of floor plans\
or photos are minimized.\
